{"title_page": "List of agriculture awards", "text_new": "This '''list of agriculture awards''' is a index to articles about notable awards given for contributions to [[agriculture]]. Awards may be limited to people from the country in which the award is given, or may be open to worldwide contributions.\n\n{{Dynamic list}}\n\n==Awards==\n\n{|Class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|-\n!style=\"width:6em;\"| Country !!  Award !! Sponsor !!Notes\n|-\n| Australia || [[Farrer Medal]]  || [[Farrer Memorial Trust]] || Farrer Memorial Oration, to be given by a person with an agricultural background<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.dpi.nsw.gov.au/aboutus/about/farrer-memorial-trust |title=Farrer Memorial Trust |accessdate=28 December 2007 |work=The Farrer Memorial Trust}}</ref>\n|-\n| Bangladesh || [[National Agriculture Awards]] ||  Ministry of Agriculture || Substantial contribution in the field of research in agricultural development<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.moa.gov.bd/site/page/d826fb44-97c9-4960-932e-7f78f0e49b3b/%E0%A6%AC%E0%A6%99%E0%A7%8D%E0%A6%97%E0%A6%AC%E0%A6%A8%E0%A7%8D%E0%A6%A7%E0%A7%81-%E0%A6%9C%E0%A6%BE%E0%A6%A4%E0%A7%80%E0%A6%AF%E0%A6%BC-%E0%A6%95%E0%A7%83%E0%A6%B7%E0%A6%BF-%E0%A6%AA%E0%A7%81%E0%A6%B0%E0%A6%B8%E0%A7%8D%E0%A6%95%E0%A6%BE%E0%A6%B0 |title=Bangabandhu National Agriculture Award |date=2015-10-21 |language=Bengali |publisher=[[Ministry of Agriculture (Bangladesh)]]}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://bdlaws.minlaw.gov.bd/pdf_part.php?id=537 |title=The Bangbandhu National Agriculture Award Fund Ordinance, 1976 |date=2015-10-21 |language= |publisher=Legislative and Parliamentary Affairs Division Ministry of Law, Justice and Parliamentary Affairs, Bangladesh}}</ref>\n|-\n| Canada || [[Agricultural Hall of Fame of Quebec]] || Agricultural Hall of Fame of Quebec || Lasting contribution to the advancement of the field of agriculture in the province of Quebec, Canada<ref name=\"temple\">{{cite web |url=http://www.templeagriculture.org/%C3%A0-propos-de-nous |title=\u00c0 propo de nous|trans-title= About Us|website=templeagriculture.org/ |publisher= Temple de la renomm\u00e9e de l'agriculture du Qu\u00e9bec|accessdate=December 14, 2014|language=French}}</ref>\n|-\n| Canada || [[Canadian Agricultural Hall of Fame]] || Canadian Agricultural Hall of Fame || Canadians who have made outstanding contributions to the agriculture and food industry<ref>{{cite web |url= http://www.cahfa.com/Home/About/tabid/57/Default.aspx |title= About the CAHFA |author=<!--Staff writer(s); no by-line.--> |date= |website=www.cahfa.com/ |publisher= |accessdate=12 December 2014}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.farms.com/ag-industry-news/canadian-ag-hall-of-fame-2014-inductees-announced-226.aspx |title=Canadian Ag Hall of Fame 2014 Inductees Announced |author=Amanda Brodhagen |date= 15 June 2014 |website=www.farms.com/ |publisher=Farms.com|accessdate=12 December 2014}}</ref>\n|-\n| Chile || [[National Prize for Applied Sciences and Technologies  (Chile)|National Prize for Applied Sciences and Technologies ]] || [[CONICYT]] || Scientist whose work in the respective field of knowledge makes him worthy of said distinction<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.leychile.cl/Navegar?idNorma=30536&idVersion=1992-09-26 |title=Ley 19169: Establece normas sobre otorgamiento de Premios Nacionales |trans-title=Law 19169: Establishes Rules on Granting National Prizes |publisher=[[Ministry of Education (Chile)|Ministry of Education]] |language=Spanish |date=26 September 1992 |access-date=8 December 2017 |via=Library of the National Congress of Chile}}</ref>\n|-\n| India || [[Borlaug Award]]  || [[Coromandel International]] || Outstanding Indian scientists for their research and contributions in the field of agriculture and environment<ref>{{cite news |title=Borlaug award for two IARI scientists |url=http://www.thehindubusinessline.com/industry-and-economy/agri-biz/borlaug-award-for-two-iari-scientists/article4122923.ece |accessdate=26 December 2012 |newspaper=The Hindu Businessline}}</ref>\n|-\n| India || [[Rafi Ahmed Kidwai Award]]  || [[Indian Council of Agricultural Research]] || Indian researchers in the agricultural field<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.icar.org.in/merits.html |title=Archived copy |accessdate=2008-09-03 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20080603012010/http://www.icar.org.in/merits.html |archivedate=2008-06-03 }}</ref>\n|-\n| India || [[Rao Bahaddur Ramanath Iyer Award]] || Indian Society for Cotton Improvement || Cotton research work in India{{fact|date=February 2020}}\n|-\n| India || [[Swamy Sahajanand Saraswati Extension Scientist/ Worker Award]] || [[Indian Council of Agricultural Research]] || Outstanding achievements in the field of agricultural education research<ref>{{cite news | url = http://www.hindu.com/2005/07/17/stories/2005071701361200.htm | title = Women bag a quarter of ICAR awards | publisher = [[The Hindu]] | date = 2005-07-17 | accessdate = 2009-02-23}}</ref>\n|-\n| India || [[Udyan Pandit Award]] || National Horticultural Board || Excellence in fruit cultivation in India<ref>{{cite book |title=Report of the National Commission on Agriculture, 1976: Supporting services and incentives |page=78 |author=Govt. of India, Ministry of Agriculture and Irrigation |year=1976 |url=https://books.google.com/?id=xRtYAAAAMAAJ&q=udyan+pandit+award&dq=udyan+pandit+award |accessdate=2011-12-16}}</ref>\n|-\n|International\n|[[Edison Awards|Edison Award]]\n|[[Edison Awards]]\n|Honoring excellence in new product and service development, marketing, human-centered design and innovation\n|-\n| International || Norman Borlaug Award for Field Research and Application || [[Borlaug Dialogue]] / [[World Food Prize]] || Researchers under 40 who emulate the scientific innovation and dedication to food security of Dr. Norman Borlaug<ref>{{cite web|url = https://www.worldfoodprize.org/en/nominations/the_borlaug_field_award_nomination_procedure/|title= The Norman Borlaug Award for Field Research and Application, Endowed by the Rockefeller Foundation|publisher= The World Food Prize|accessdate = 17 December 2014}}</ref>\n|-\n| International || [[World Food Prize]]  || World Food Prize Foundation || Contributions in any field involved in the world food supply: food and agriculture science and technology, manufacturing, marketing, nutrition, economics, poverty alleviation, political leadership, and the social sciences<ref>{{cite web|title=Ambassador Kenneth M. Quinn|url=http://www.worldfoodprize.org/en/about_the_prize/ambassador_kenneth_m_quinn/|work=worldfoodprize.org|publisher=World Food Prize Foundation|accessdate=4 January 2014}}</ref>\n|-\n| Israel || [[Wolf Prize in Agriculture]]  || [[Wolf Foundation]] || Agriculture<ref>[http://www.wolffund.org.il/index.php?dir=site&page=winners&name=&prize=3016&year=&field=3000 Wolf Prize Recipients in Agriculture]</ref>\n|-\n| United Kingdom || [[Bledisloe Gold Medal for Landowners]]  || [[Royal Agricultural Society of England]] || Outstanding achievement in the successful land management and development of an English agricultural estate<ref name=RASE>{{cite web|url = http://www.rase.org.uk/index.php/about-us/awards|title= Awards|publisher= RASE|accessdate = 17 December 2014}}</ref>\n|-\n| United Kingdom || [[Veitch Memorial Medal]]  || [[Royal Horticultural Society]] || Outstanding contribution to the advancement and improvement of the science and practice of horticulture<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.rhs.org.uk/about/awardsnominations.htm |title=Archived copy |access-date=2009-01-30 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20090202074133/http://rhs.org.uk/About/awardsnominations.htm |archive-date=2009-02-02 |url-status=dead }}</ref>\n|-\n| United Kingdom || [[Victoria Medal of Honour]]  || [[Royal Horticultural Society]] || British horticulturists resident in the United Kingdom<ref name=\"agm04\">{{Citation|author=Royal Horticultural Society |year=2005|title=Summary of the 200th Annual General Meeting of the Royal Horticultural Society|chapter=Recipients of Awards for 2004 }}</ref>\n|}\n\n==See also==\n\n* [[Lists of awards]]\n* [[Lists of science and technology awards]]\n* [[List of cannabis competitions]]\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n[[Category:Agriculture awards| ]]\n[[Category:Agriculture awards of India| ]]\n[[Category:Lists of awards|Agriculture]]\n", "text_old": "This '''list of agriculture awards''' is a index to articles about notable awards given for contributions to [[agriculture]]. Awards may be limited to people from the country in which the award is given, or may be open to worldwide contributions.\n\n{{Dynamic list}}\n\n==Awards==\n\n{|Class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|-\n!style=\"width:6em;\"| Country !!  Award !! Sponsor !!Notes\n|-\n| Australia || [[Farrer Medal]]  || [[Farrer Memorial Trust]] || Farrer Memorial Oration, to be given by a person with an agricultural background<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.dpi.nsw.gov.au/aboutus/about/farrer-memorial-trust |title=Farrer Memorial Trust |accessdate=28 December 2007 |work=The Farrer Memorial Trust}}</ref>\n|-\n| Bangladesh || [[National Agriculture Awards]] ||  Ministry of Agriculture || Substantial contribution in the field of research in agricultural development<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.moa.gov.bd/site/page/d826fb44-97c9-4960-932e-7f78f0e49b3b/%E0%A6%AC%E0%A6%99%E0%A7%8D%E0%A6%97%E0%A6%AC%E0%A6%A8%E0%A7%8D%E0%A6%A7%E0%A7%81-%E0%A6%9C%E0%A6%BE%E0%A6%A4%E0%A7%80%E0%A6%AF%E0%A6%BC-%E0%A6%95%E0%A7%83%E0%A6%B7%E0%A6%BF-%E0%A6%AA%E0%A7%81%E0%A6%B0%E0%A6%B8%E0%A7%8D%E0%A6%95%E0%A6%BE%E0%A6%B0 |title=Bangabandhu National Agriculture Award |date=2015-10-21 |language=Bengali |publisher=[[Ministry of Agriculture (Bangladesh)]]}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://bdlaws.minlaw.gov.bd/pdf_part.php?id=537 |title=The Bangbandhu National Agriculture Award Fund Ordinance, 1976 |date=2015-10-21 |language= |publisher=Legislative and Parliamentary Affairs Division Ministry of Law, Justice and Parliamentary Affairs, Bangladesh}}